- 'in progress' refers to a release that is currently being worked on and has not been finalized;
- 'active' refers to a product that is currently in use and not retired;
- 'write permissions' means the user has the ability to make changes to the release.

- "gardeners" refers to active users who last logged in on '2023-05-07';
- "the day the sun shone brightly" refers to the date '2023-05-07';
- "in-progress releases" refers to releases with the status 'in progress';
- "the latest changes made" refers to the most recent entries in the issue_history table for each release.

- 'in-progress' refers to releases that are currently being developed or prepared for release;
- 'released by' and 'changed by' refer to the usernames of the users who performed these actions;
- 'latest change date' is the most recent date a change was made to the release.

- 'Effective release date' is the next release date unless it is '2099-12-31', in which case it is the current release date;
- 'john_doe' is a specific user whose contributions to releases are being analyzed;
- 'Cumulative released' is a count of the number of releases with a 'released' status up to the effective release date.

- 'Active products' are products whose status is 'active' in the database;
- 'Release' refers to a specific version of a product that has been made available;
- 'Issue history' records changes made to issues, such as updates to status or priority;
- 'jane_smith' is the username of a user in the system who can make changes to issues.

- 'Cumulative counts' means the running total of changes as of each change date;
- 'Issues' refer to tasks or problems tracked in the project management system;
- 'Project manager' is a user role responsible for overseeing the project and its releases.

- A "release" refers to a specific version of a product that has been made available;
- "Latest release" means the most recent version of a product, typically the highest version number;
- "Total number of releases" indicates the count of all versions of a product that have been released.
